Sentencas: In this study, perovskite oxides SrFe1-xCuxO3-delta are systematically evaluated as potential cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Insights into the oxygen reduction reaction on Cu-doped SrFeO3-δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Cu doping is found to decrease the unit cell volume, while the average valence of iron and the oxygen vacancy content increase steadily in SrFe1-xCuxO3-delta.
Titulo: Insights into the oxygen reduction reaction on Cu-doped SrFeO3-δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The conductivity relaxation test proves that the higher the doping amount of Cu, the larger the D-chem and k(chem) values of the material.
Titulo: Insights into the oxygen reduction reaction on Cu-doped SrFeO3-δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Among the copper doped materials, SrFe0.7Cu0.3O3-delta shows the best catalytic performance for oxygen reduction reaction.
Titulo: Insights into the oxygen reduction reaction on Cu-doped SrFeO3-δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance is 0.107 Omega cm(2), and the peak power density reaches 858 mW cm(-2) at 700 degrees
